"We have the old buildings, lots of veteran trees and a host of favorable habitats.
But there is a lot about bats that are still unknown, so the work we do here and on other properties helps us understand more about what they need to thrive.
He emphasizes the importance of searching for bats before performing maintenance in real estate, as it is possible that accidental destruction of a single dwell could kill up to 400 females and young people, and possibly wipe out an entire population.
Fladder mice are peaceful and it is illegal to kill, bother or disturb them or destroy their bon.
Elisabeth Ferrell, Scottish officer of the Bat Conservation Trust, has encouraged the public to help.
